Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.41,0:01:00.29,Title,,0,0,250,,{\bord0\4a&HFF&\blur0.7\fad(800,0)}The Empty Throne
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.67,0:01:12.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Kaido-{\i1}sama{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.09,0:01:17.72,Main,,0,0,0,,What is it?!\NDon't bother me when I'm drinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.72,0:01:20.18,Main,,0,0,0,,No! I didn't mean to!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.18,0:01:21.31,Main,,0,0,0,,The thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.15,0:01:36.11,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What do you want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.95,0:01:39.32,Main,,0,0,0,,It's about Straw Hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.32,0:01:42.54,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's on his way to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.54,0:01:44.91,Main,,0,0,0,,{So what?}What are you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.91,0:01:48.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Listen, keep your hands off him!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.38,0:01:53.63,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm coming to Wano to claim Straw Hat's head myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.26,0:01:57.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Is this some kind of {a }joke?! I refuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.34,0:02:00.09,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have no business with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.93,0:02:06.39,Main,,0,0,0,,{I've got to take Straw Hat out, or I'll lose face!}If I don't personally squash Straw Hat, \N{my reputation will suffer}I'll become a laughingstock.{Zenef: I like the original line "I'll lose face" but it's much shorter than the spoken line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.39,0:02:10.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Besides, he has something that I want back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.23,0:02:11.94,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't care!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.32,0:02:15.90,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You still owe me big time, {right}don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.90,0:02:17.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Owe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.53,0:02:20.16,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{You remember, don't you?}Don't tell me you've forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.16,0:02:22.37,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That was a long time ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.37,0:02:25.24,Main,,0,0,0,,{But...}{No matter!}Even so, it was a {lifetime}lifelong debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.00,0:02:37.05,Main,,0,0,0,,{I'm the one who's got a grudge against that Straw Hat brat!}I'm the one who'll get even \Nwith that Straw Hat rookie!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.05,0:02:39.72,Main,,0,0,0,,So {\i1}I'm{\i0} the one who'll kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.72,0:02:43.43,Main,,0,0,0,,{If you come, I'll kill you too, Linlin!}Show your face, and I'll kill you too, Linlin!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.43,0:02:45.22,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'd like to see you try.{I didn't call to get your permission, I'm just giving you fair warning.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.22,0:02:48.73,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm not asking your permission;\Nthis is merely a courtesy call.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.60,0:02:54.69,Main,,0,0,0,,{Get it}Got that? Straw Hat's head is mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.69,0:02:58.99,Main,,0,0,0,,{Let's try and get along... like we used to!}So let's play nice... for old times' sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.87,0:03:04.53,Main,,0,0,3,,Big Mom is on the move!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.53,0:03:07.41,Main,,0,0,3,,It {appears that}seems she's contacted Kaido!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.41,0:03:09.75,Main,,0,0,0,,They're using an unsecured channel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.75,0:03:14.84,Main,,0,0,0,,{They don't care about being wiretapped}Don't they care if we overhear?!\NAre they {\i1}trying{\i0} to provoke us?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.46,0:03:17.92,Main,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{Let's try and get along...}So let's play nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:22.39,Main,,0,0,0,,{What could oppose both \NEmperor Big Mom and Emperor Kaido?}What force could possibly oppose \NEmperor Big Mom and Emperor Kaido?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.39,0:03:25.26,Main,,0,0,0,,{The admirals}Admirals? The Seven Warlords?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.89,0:03:31.73,Main,,0,0,0,,{Do you want me to head out, Sakazuki?}Should I head out, Sakazuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.73,0:03:34.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait, Borsalino.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.48,0:03:39.32,Main,,0,0,0,,{We don't know the military capability of Wano.}We have zero intel on {the military might of Wano}Wano's military capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.15,0:03:42.20,Main,,0,0,0,,{The samurai, huh?}Their samurai, you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.53,0:03:47.20,Main,,0,0,3,,Seriously?! Garp-{\i1}chan{\fs10} {\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.20,0:03:51.75,Main,,0,0,0,,{Aren't Kaido and Big Mom going after your grandson?!}Don't Kaido and Big Mom each have \Na bone to pick with your grandson?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.75,0:03:54.38,Main,,0,0,0,,{Straw Hat Luffy!}With Straw Hat Luffy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.09,0:03:57.67,Main,,0,0,0,,{That's hilarious!}What a riot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.38,0:04:02.18,Main,,0,0,0,,{This isn't a joke!}You realize this isn't a joke, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.59,0:04:07.14,Main,,0,0,3,,{Are you just going to allow two of the emperors to team up?}You're saying you'd just let two emperors team up?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.14,0:04:11.39,Main,,0,0,0,,{Well, it's not like we can do anything anyway;\Nit's the Reverie!}It's not as if we can do anything right now. \NNot during the Reverie anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.39,0:04:15.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Most of our manpower has been \Nassigned to protect {the royals}royalty!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.23,0:04:17.19,Main,,0,0,0,,But if nothing is done...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.19,0:04:19.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Pardon me, ma'am,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.82,0:04:22.07,Main,,0,0,0,,but this is Big Mom we're {talking}talkin' about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.07,0:04:25.41,Main,,0,0,0,,{\q2}{She must have known that the Navy couldn't spare any marines...}She must've known the Navy ain't gonna spare a soul,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.41,0:04:28.03,Main,,0,0,0,,{because of the Reverie!}what with the Reverie!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.03,0:04:29.99,Main,,0,0,0,,You're right, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.99,0:04:32.54,Main,,0,0,0,,What did Mister Sakazuki say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.54,0:04:36.96,Main,,0,0,0,,He said, "Wano is a not a member country,\Nso it's outside our jurisdiction."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.96,0:04:38.63,Main,,0,0,0,,{Just as I'd expect!}Figured as much!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.38,0:04:42.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Best not to get involved for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.51,0:04:47.30,Main,,0,0,0,,But Garp-{\i1}kun{\i},
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.30,0:04:50.10,Main,,0,0,2,,if Big Mom and Kaido are up to something again,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.10,0:04:52.39,Main,,0,0,2,,we shouldn't take it lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.39,0:04:53.39,Main,,0,0,2,,After all,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:57.31,Main,,0,0,0,,{you became known as the hero of the Navy because of them...}they're the reason you're \Nknown as the "{h}Hero of the Navy."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.48,0:05:01.28,Main,,0,0,0,,{The "Rocks", huh?}Rocks, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.28,0:05:08.03,Main,,0,0,0,,{Hina, you're quite young.\NWhere did you hear about this?}Hina, I'd've guessed you'd be \Ntoo young to hear about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.28,0:05:13.25,Main,,0,0,0,,{Before Roger, it was definitely their era!}Before Roger, that era belonged to {\i1}them{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.00,0:05:18.42,Main,,0,0,0,,But that was 40 years ago.\NThe past is in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.42,0:05:22.38,Main,,0,0,0,,{Even though}Though they lost their captain,\N{they're still gaining influence.}their influence only grows.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.38,0:05:24.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Hina's worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.09,0:05:26.18,Main,,0,0,0,,No point worrying!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.18,0:05:31.97,Main,,0,0,0,,{True, they would be a threat if they returned,\Nbut things never turn out how you'd expect anyway...}True, they'd be a threat if they returned,\Nbut the future always finds ways to surprise us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.97,0:05:37.40,Main,,0,0,0,,{Your grandson's bounty is also a real problem.}But seriously, that bounty on your grandson's\Na real nuisance, ain't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.40,0:05:41.15,Main,,0,0,0,,{I mean, it jumped to 1.5 billion belly.}It recently jumped to 1.5 billion belly, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.28,0:05:46.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Why are you smiling? Hina's confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.24,0:05:49.28,Main,,0,0,0,,{He's still just a fledgling.}And he's still just getting started...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.95,0:05:53.54,Main,,0,0,1,,You may enter, King Sterry of Goa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.52,0:06:21.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,So {\i1}this{\i0} is the center of the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.20,0:06:38.62,Main,,0,0,0,,– Now, swear your oath.{..}\N– What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.62,0:06:40.88,Main,,0,0,0,,C-Can I sit there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.88,0:06:43.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't joke about such things!{Is that supposed to be a joke?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.21,0:06:44.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,Tch!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.17,0:06:48.34,Main,,0,0,0,,No one is allowed to sit upon that throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.34,0:06:50.59,Main,,0,0,0,,It is the Empty Throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.59,0:06:53.43,Main,,0,0,0,,It symbolizes equality between the {rulers of nations.}nations' leaders.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.43,0:06:56.97,Main,,0,0,0,,The oath affirms that no ruler\Nwill seek dominion over the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.97,0:07:00.39,Main,,0,0,0,,The 20 weapons {that protect the throne...}that stand sentinel over the throne...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.39,0:07:07.57,Main,,0,0,0,,were placed there 800 years ago to represent \Nthe oaths of the First Twenty, {who created the world.}the world's creators.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.57,0:07:11.11,Main,,0,0,0,,It is located at the very center of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.11,0:07:14.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Its vacancy is evidence of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.66,0:07:23.21,Main,,0,0,0,,{The greatest authority in the world remains with the Five Elders, the highest-ranking Celestial Dragons.}{While}As the Five Elders, the {highest-ranking}Celestial Dragons' leadership, remain the greatest authority in the world,{Not the greatest sentence structure here...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:27.71,Main,,0,0,0,,{There is no one ruler of the world.}their division of {leadership}power symbolizes how there is no one ruler over all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.43,0:07:35.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, swear your oath, King Sterry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.26,0:07:40.81,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,If I sit there, I'll be king of the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.81,0:07:42.56,Main,,0,0,0,,King Sterry?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.35,0:07:47.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,I wanna sit there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.15,0:07:53.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.49,0:07:54.49,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.03,0:07:57.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Please stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.20,0:08:01.96,Main,,0,0,1,,I caught one-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.96,0:08:04.83,Main,,0,0,1,,I caught a giant mermaid-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.83,0:08:06.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Shirahoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.76,0:08:12.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Father{-}{\i1}{sama}{\i}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.22,0:08:16.64,Main,,0,0,0,,{How can we forgive such an outrage}Do you expect us to overlook \Nsuch disrespect, Father{-}{sama}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:22.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Come on! Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.06,0:08:25.52,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?! Please stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.52,0:08:27.90,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right! Chain her up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:31.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Shirahoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.19,0:08:34.36,Main,,0,0,0,,{Wait}Hold it! What are you doing,\NPrincess of Arabasta?!{Open to ideas, but what he's saying is fairly straightforward}{Gaijin, this sounds a bit stiff. Can we take any liberties with this one?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.36,0:08:35.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Shirahoshi-{\i1}chan{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.78,0:08:39.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Stop, Rebecca! He's a Celestial Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.12,0:08:41.33,Main,,0,0,0,,So what?! Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.33,0:08:46.33,Main,,0,0,0,,{They have no perspective}They lack common sense!\NIf you anger them, they'll destroy Dressrosa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.63,0:08:55.89,Main,,0,0,0,,That bastard{...}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.89,0:08:57.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't do it, Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.22,0:08:59.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Shirahoshi{...}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.36,0:09:11.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Whoa, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.65,0:09:13.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,No one interfere!{Hard to say, but the manga seems to have him thinking it. His mouth doesn't look like it's speaking.}{Do you think he's actually saying this, or do we leave this in the Thoughts style?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.45,0:09:17.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.62,0:09:27.29,Main,,0,0,0,,{Do it}Capture it, Slave #3!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.29,0:09:30.84,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll make it my pet-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.42,0:09:38.47,Main,,0,0,0,,{I can't just stand here!\NHow dare he do that to our boss' friend!}No standin' around!\NHe's gonna pay for doin' this to our boss' friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.47,0:09:41.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.27,0:09:45.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Damn! {I have no choice!}There's no other way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.48,0:09:48.23,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm coming for you, Mermaid Princess!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.23,0:09:51.40,Main,,0,0,0,,– Don't do it, Kanese soldier!\N– Somebody, stop him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.69,0:09:57.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.91,0:10:01.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.87,0:10:03.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Who are you bastards?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.87,0:10:09.29,Main,,0,0,3,,{\an8}You should be thanking me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.29,0:10:11.63,Main,,0,0,3,,{\an8}Cipher Pol 0.{..}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.55,0:10:14.67,Main,,0,0,3,,{\an8}{Indeed, by stopping you...}Yes indeedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.67,0:10:16.92,Main,,0,0,3,,{\an8}{we just saved several countries.}Stopping you just spared several countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.92,0:10:19.39,Main,,0,0,3,,{\an8}{You do not cross a Celestial Dragon.}Don't ruffle the feathers of Celestial Dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.39,0:10:21.10,Main,,0,0,3,,{\an8}{Even children know that.}Even young 'uns know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.52,0:10:30.06,Main,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}Cipher Pol is a secret organization\Nunder the direct control of the World Government.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.06,0:10:36.53,Main,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}Aegis 0 is the top unit in the agency,\N{with}boasting the most powerful agents.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.99,0:10:42.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Sai!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.29,0:10:49.29,Main,,0,0,0,,The Celestial Dragons are the gods\Nwho created this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.29,0:10:52.71,Main,,0,0,0,,{And all of you are merely the royals of the lower realm.}And though you are royalty, \Nyou merely rule the lower realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.71,0:10:56.76,Main,,0,0,0,,It's only natural for gods to get whatever they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.76,0:10:59.18,Main,,0,0,0,,He's right-{\i1}{eh}ee{\i}, you {idiots}nincompoops!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.18,0:11:02.01,Main,,0,0,0,,{That doesn't make sense!}Where's the logic in that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.01,0:11:04.56,Main,,0,0,0,,{A god need not make sense.}Why would a god need logic?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:06.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Vivi-{\i1}chan-sama{\i}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.77,0:11:12.31,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,Otohime{...},
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.31,0:11:16.36,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,your dream was to live side-by-side with humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.36,0:11:18.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,in a world of sunlight!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.78,0:11:22.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Give me back Shirahoshi! She's my friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.75,0:11:32.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait, Princess of Arabasta!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.17,0:11:33.79,Main,,0,0,0,,King Neptune!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.79,0:11:37.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you! {I won't forget your kindness!}I'll never forget your kindness!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.88,0:11:41.97,Main,,0,0,0,,But I'm afraid I must let go of our dreams-{\i1}jamon{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.97,0:11:43.09,Main,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.18,0:11:51.23,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll crush them, and we'll return to our seafloor home-{\i1}jamon{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.23,0:11:56.86,Main,,0,0,0,,No! Don't hit him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.86,0:12:00.99,Main,,0,0,0,,If this {is the norm}is what happens on the surface,\N{I can't bring my people here anyway!}I can never bring my people here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.99,0:12:03.28,Main,,0,0,0,,No! This isn't how it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.70,0:12:06.37,Main,,0,0,0,,King Neptune! This is not humanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.70,0:12:12.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Otohime{...}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.58,0:12:17.46,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Let's face them together!{Pepperjack, here's another flashback for you.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.46,0:12:25.72,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Then maybe we can make a difference\Nfor the future of the children on this island,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.05,0:12:29.31,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,{\t(1693,2250,1,\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&)}even just a small one!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.68,0:12:36.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{Even if we were to love them,\Nhumans won't change!}Even if we gave them our love,\Nwe can't change human nature!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.19,0:12:39.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,I have to save Shirahoshi{...}; forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.78,0:12:43.36,Main,,0,0,0,,How dare you defy me?\NKill him, Cipher Pol 0!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.36,0:12:43.90,Main,,0,0,0,,{Roger.}{Yes, sir.}Wilco.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:45.41,Main,,0,0,0,,{Get out of my way!}Out of my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.41,0:12:48.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Great Knight Neptune!\NDon't be {a fool}hasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.33,0:12:54.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Father{-}{\i1}{sama}{\i}{...}, no!\N{We should not give in to hatred!}Let go of your hatred!{Anakin!}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.76,0:13:06.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Ugh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.14,0:13:12.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Who hit the Celestial Dragon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.27,0:13:16.23,Main,,0,0,0,,I-I have nothing to do with these hippos!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.73,0:13:24.86,Main,,0,0,0,,{I'm sorry...\NAs a fellow Celestial Dragon, I feel ashamed!}I'm so sorry!\NAs a fellow Celestial Dragon, I feel nothing but shame!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.07,0:13:27.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Please forgive us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.37,0:13:31.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Is he a Celestial Dragon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.29,0:13:34.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Let go of the princess, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.67,0:13:38.50,Main,,0,0,0,,My apologies{ to}, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.50,0:13:41.84,Main,,0,0,0,,This fool {brought panic to a place meant for socializing!}induced panic \Nwhere we should be peaceably socializing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.05,0:13:47.80,Main,,0,0,0,,I assume you don't remember me, Neptune.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.47,0:13:54.56,Main,,0,0,0,,But I am indebted to the Ryugu Kingdom\N{and have been waiting for this day!}and have patiently awaited this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.56,0:13:57.48,Main,,0,0,0,,{The day that you would come here!}The day you would arrive here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.40,0:14:00.15,Main,,0,0,0,,{Don't tell me you're...}That means... you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.07,0:14:06.57,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm the foolish Celestial Dragon...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.57,0:14:10.03,Main,,0,0,0,,who drifted down to \Nthe Ryugu Kingdom a decade ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.66,0:14:14.16,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and save me, you {fool}imbeciles!{Yet another flashback, Pepperjack!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.25,0:14:19.38,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,– Kill him!\N– Make him suffer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.38,0:14:20.92,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Show him no mercy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.92,0:14:22.13,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.13,0:14:24.05,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,{\t(1343,1802,1,\c&H000000&\3c&H000000&)}You stupid fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.06,0:14:39.44,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Queen Otohime!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.44,0:14:41.61,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,The {queen has}queen's been shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.41,0:14:53.95,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Queen Otohime{...}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.41,0:14:58.29,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Everybody, drop your guns!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.75,0:15:02.75,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Children are watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.55,0:15:11.14,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Otohime-{\i1}sama{\i}{...}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.97,0:15:14.89,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,It's just a scratch.{It's just a flesh wound.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.89,0:15:16.39,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Why are you protecting him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.39,0:15:19.94,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,{Don't you know what he did to us in the past?!}You know what he's done to us all!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.94,0:15:24.36,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,{I can feel your anguish - it must be hard!}I understand your anguish;\N{it must be hard!}the pain runs deep for me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.98,0:15:27.11,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,{I understand}Our hearts ache, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.11,0:15:33.37,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,{you shouldn't spread your}we mustn't teach our resentment\Nof humans {to the children here}to our children!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.33,0:15:39.08,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,They should get the chance to meet humans and decide for themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.58,0:15:46.00,Main,,0,0,1,,The words of the late Queen Otohime...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.00,0:15:48.17,Main,,0,0,1,,{made me human!}gave me my humanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.17,0:15:50.80,Main,,0,0,1,,I would do anything to help your people!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.34,0:15:56.35,Main,,0,0,0,,King Neptune{! It's}, it is an honor to see you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.35,0:15:59.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Cipher Pol! Leave this place!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.26,0:16:41.31,Main,,0,0,0,,{Why did you need to come all the way here?}What would compel you to come all this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.31,0:16:43.14,Main,,0,0,0,,The Reverie is at hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.14,0:16:47.52,Main,,0,0,0,,{You are in no position to be involved in politics.}Your position normally precludes any political entanglement.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.02,0:16:50.73,Main,,0,0,0,,We only made time because it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.73,0:16:54.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes... and I appreciate that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.07,0:16:57.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's hear it, then.\NGuards, would you excuse us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.78,0:16:58.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:20.18,Main,,0,0,0,,I need to talk to you about a certain pirate...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.94,0:17:31.02,Main,,0,0,0,,{Most of the people are gone...}The crowd's really thinned out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.02,0:17:33.74,Main,,0,0,0,,It's to be expected\Nafter a mess like that.{After such a scene, \Nwhat do you expect?!}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.74,0:17:37.91,Main,,0,0,0,,No one wants to get involved in a scandal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.12,0:17:44.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow{...}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.54,0:17:47.75,Main,,0,0,0,,How's that, Shirahoshi-{\i1}san{\fs12} {\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.63,0:17:51.92,Main,,0,0,0,,The bruise is completely gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.92,0:17:55.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Mansherry-{\i1}chan-sama{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.92,0:17:57.97,Main,,0,0,0,,{That's}What a wonderful ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.93,0:18:07.85,Main,,0,0,0,,{I think you two are the biggest princess\Nand the smallest princess in the world!}{To}I think we{'d} have both the world's \Nbiggest and smallest princesses right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.27,0:18:11.98,Main,,0,0,0,,{I'm sorry that I was\Nafraid of you at first...}I admit you frightened me at first. \NI'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.98,0:18:15.99,Main,,0,0,0,,{I don't mind at all}I'm not bothered in the least, \NMansherry-{\i1}chan-sama{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.95,0:18:22.08,Main,,0,0,0,,{I suppose all countries have both\Ngood people and bad people.}It seems all countries \Nare comprised of both good and bad people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.08,0:18:25.79,Main,,0,0,0,,The fishmen are no exception-{\i1}jamon{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.79,0:18:30.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks to you,\NI kept my promise to Otohime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.54,0:18:33.88,Main,,0,0,0,,No need to thank me, Neptune!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.88,0:18:37.09,Main,,0,0,0,,I want to return the favor\Nfor saving me 10 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.09,0:18:42.18,Main,,0,0,0,,{During the seven days of the conference,\NI'll look after Princess Shirahoshi.}For the duration of this conference's seven days,\NI'll keep a close watch over Princess Shirahoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.18,0:18:46.27,Main,,0,0,0,,If my status can help, I'll gladly make use of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.27,0:18:50.15,Main,,0,0,0,,I've been told that I should keep \Nmy hands off of the Celestial Dragons,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.15,0:18:54.48,Main,,0,0,0,,{but could I kick their butts\Nif it's on your orders?}but if you gave the order, \Ncould I kick their butts?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.48,0:18:58.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes! If it's necessary to protect\Nthe princess and her companions,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.61,0:19:01.49,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll take full responsibility!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.12,0:19:08.71,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't believe an oddball like him exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.71,0:19:10.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Vivi-{\i1}sama{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.75,0:19:17.38,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Vivi-{\i1}sama{\i}. \NI heard there was trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.38,0:19:19.38,Main,,0,0,0,,I should've {stayed with you.}been at your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.38,0:19:22.59,Main,,0,0,0,,{Don't worry}Rest easy, Pell. I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.59,0:19:24.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Anyway, how's Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.43,0:19:27.97,Main,,0,0,0,,{Cobra-sama is talking to Admiral Fujitora of the Navy,\Nthe one who sent that letter.}Cobra-{\i1}sama{\i0} is talking \Nto the one who sent that letter:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.97,0:19:29.89,Main,,0,0,0,,{Cobra-sama is talking to Admiral Fujitora of the Navy,\Nthe one who sent that letter.}Admiral Fujitora of the Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.89,0:19:33.27,Main,,0,0,0,,They're {having a conversation}conversing with King Riku of Dressrosa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.27,0:19:34.69,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.{..}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.65,0:19:40.57,Main,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}Pangaea Castle has...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.57,0:19:45.28,Main,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}three gates outside of its main gate,\Nand all of them are guarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.66,0:19:50.54,Main,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}{One of those gates is \Nthe Celestial Dragon Gate...}Most notable is the Celestial Dragon Gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.54,0:19:54.38,Main,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}which leads to the Land of the Gods\Nwhere the Celestial Dragons reside.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.18,0:20:05.89,Main,,0,0,0,,Stop! Who goes there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.31,0:20:14.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Why, {you're}if it isn't Queen Dowager Conney of {the }Sorbet{ Kingdom}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.28,0:20:22.70,Main,,0,0,0,,The Land of the Gods is beyond this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.70,0:20:26.62,Main,,0,0,0,,You can't pass; it's dangerous to be here.\NPlease {go back}return to the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.62,0:20:32.71,Main,,0,0,0,,It hurts-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}! It's unforgivable-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!\NDamn that Mjosgard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.71,0:20:35.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Saint Charlos! Please be calm!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.46,0:20:37.42,Main,,0,0,0,,You'll aggravate your wounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.42,0:20:41.30,Main,,0,0,0,,He can't get away with this-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.30,0:20:43.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Open the gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.38,0:20:46.34,Main,,0,0,0,,What?! What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.34,0:20:48.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Saint Charlos is {hurt}injured!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:20:51.14,Main,,0,0,0,,He requires urgent {treatment}care!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.14,0:20:52.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.78,0:21:04.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Hurry up! He requires medical assistance!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.53,0:21:14.00,Main,,0,0,1,,Oh, Charlos! Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.00,0:21:18.71,Main,,0,0,0,,I heard what happened.\NI was on my way to pick you up-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.71,0:21:20.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Saint Rosward!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.46,0:21:23.59,Main,,0,0,0,,F-Father{-}{\i1}{sama}{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.63,0:21:28.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, look at you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.68,0:21:31.22,Main,,0,0,0,,My dearest son!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.35,0:21:37.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.69,0:21:39.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Where did the queen dowager go?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.36,0:21:44.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Damn that Mjosgard! I'll make him pay for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.40,0:21:46.61,Main,,0,0,0,,He's always been a strange man:
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.61,0:21:49.78,Main,,0,0,0,,a Celestial Dragon who doesn't own a single slave!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.78,0:21:54.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Just like Homing who descended\Nto the lower realm 30 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.08,0:21:58.75,Main,,0,0,0,,The Donquixote family {must be crazy}is full of lunatics-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.63,0:22:03.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Father{-}{\i1}{sama}{\i}, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.30,0:22:09.14,Main,,0,0,1,,the invincible slave, Kuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.14,0:22:10.85,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.85,0:22:15.56,Main,,0,0,0,,{My turn to rent him finally came}I finally got to rent him out-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.93,0:22:19.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}Bartholomew Kuma, known as “the Tyrant,”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.90,0:22:23.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}was once a universally feared pirate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.28,0:22:27.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}Few have had as checkered a life as his.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.95,0:22:31.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}Kuma, one of the Seven Warlords,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.24,0:22:36.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}{received a special assignment from the World Government...}took on a special mission from the World Government\Nto eliminate the Straw Hats.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.20,0:22:42.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}{Thus he suddenly emerged\Nin front of Luffy and the others...}He reached Thriller Bark just as Luffy\Nand the others pulled through their arduous battle. {right after their hard-fought battle on Thriller Bark.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.72,0:22:56.81,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}{36}Thirty-Six-Pound Phoenix!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.27,0:23:03.11,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,{Is that your ability?}So that's your ability?{Pepperjack, more flashbacks for you!}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.11,0:23:07.07,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,I have the power to repel things.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.07,0:23:11.74,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,I ate the Paw Paw Fruit \Nand became a {paw paw}paw pad man.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.41,0:23:18.33,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Are you truly willing to die for that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.33,0:23:23.79,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,Right now, it's the only way\Nto save my crewmates!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.79,0:23:27.84,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,My {ambition}dream means nothing\Nif I can't protect my own captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.84,0:23:31.72,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,{Luffy is gonna be king of the pirates!}Luffy will be king of the pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.10,0:23:41.56,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,He has good friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.94,0:23:47.82,Flashbacks,,0,0,0,,I should have expected no less\Nfrom your son, Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.82,0:23:52.66,Main,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}{Even though Kuma is a warlord,\Nhe disobeyed the government's orders...}Despite Kuma's status as a warlord,\Nhe disobeyed the government's orders,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.66,0:23:56.66,Main,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1\t(3677,3990,1,\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&)}and for some unknown reason,\N{spared the Straw Hats' lives.}he spared the Straw Hats' lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.25,0:24:07.55,Main,,0,0,0,,This is so exciting-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!\NFather{-}{\i1}{sama}{\i} finally got to rent the invincible slave Kuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.55,0:24:11.51,Main,,0,0,0,,It's {convenient}advantageous to have\Na warlord as a slave-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.51,0:24:13.39,Main,,0,0,0,,You can hit him!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.39,0:24:16.05,Main,,0,0,0,,You could even stab him!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.77,0:24:23.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Yet he doesn't ever scream.\NHe's a top-class slave-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.14,0:24:28.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Nice, Father{-}{\i1}{sama}{\fs10} {\r}! I want one too-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.36,0:24:31.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Ow, ow, ow{...}! I'm gonna die-{\i1}{eh}ee{\i}.{..}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.99,0:24:34.95,Main,,0,0,0,,{You must remain calm}Please stay still, Charlos-{\i1}sama{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:39.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Ow, ow, ow{...}! {I really got a thrashing}He did a number on me-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.45,0:24:42.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, poor Charlos!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.96,0:24:46.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's get the world's greatest doctor\Nto look at you-{\i1}{eh}ee{\fs10} {\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.05,0:24:54.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,I didn't expect {to}I'd see him {this}so soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.98,0:25:05.02,Thoughts,,0,0,1,,My infiltration was a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.48,0:25:12.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,I'll never forgive them!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.16,0:25:17.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{Ever!}Not ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.41,0:25:24.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.04,0:25:28.17,Main,,0,0,10,,{Don't get mad, Sabo...}Don't get in a tizzy, Sabo!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.17,0:25:31.25,Main,,0,0,10,,You boys {are so scary}can all be so scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.25,0:25:33.63,Main,,0,0,0,,{It's impossible not to get mad!}I can't help but get mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.17,0:25:37.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Our {friend}comrade is going through hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.22,0:25:39.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Our gentle Kuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.64,0:25:44.85,Main,,0,0,0,,{It's unforgivable...}It's unthinkable{...}!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.31,0:25:47.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.94,0:25:51.57,Main,,0,0,0,,We get it. We all feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.57,0:25:54.15,Main,,0,0,0,,We won't leave Kuma-{\i1}san{\i} to this fate!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.15,0:25:57.32,Main,,0,0,0,,{That's one of the reasons we came here...}After all, he's one of the reasons we came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.37,0:26:05.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Having said that, even if we set him free,\Nhe'll never return to his old self.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.50,0:26:12.50,Main,,0,0,0,,{Still}Let's not forget, Kuma-{\i1}chan{\i} is a prime example\Nof the World Government's oppression!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.50,0:26:16.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Since Kuma-{\i1}san{\i} {was formerly a king}is the former king\Nof a member nation,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.17,0:26:19.84,Main,,0,0,0,,they wanted to make \Nan example out of him as a warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.84,0:26:25.06,Main,,0,0,0,,{To show that no matter how tough you are}A warning that no matter your strength or resolve,\Nthis is how you end up if you disobey the gods!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.06,0:26:29.15,Main,,0,0,0,,The Celestial Dragons have CP-0\Nand Navy Headquarters {on their side.}in their corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.81,0:26:32.52,Main,,0,0,0,,If we fail and get caught{...}–
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.52,0:26:35.36,Main,,0,0,0,,No. Failure is not an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.86,0:26:37.82,Main,,0,0,0,,We either succeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.82,0:26:39.28,Main,,0,0,0,,or we die!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.66,0:26:50.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}It's finally time for the Reverie!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.84,0:26:53.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}The world is divided into four oceans...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.26,0:26:58.09,Narrator,,0,0,1,,{\an8\i1}by {a}the continental wall{ - the Red Line...}, the Red Line...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.09,0:27:02.93,Narrator,,0,0,1,,{\q2}{\an8\i1}and the deadly seas of the Grand Line and the New World,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.93,0:27:06.64,Narrator,,0,0,1,,{\an8\i1}{where Luffy and his crew are adventuring.}which is where Luffy and his crew are adventuring.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.48,0:27:11.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}The World Government is a truly massive organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.10,0:27:15.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}Most countries in the world are members: \N{A total of 170 nations}170 nations total!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.86,0:27:24.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}Of those, 50 monarchs are chosen as representatives to assemble in the Holy Land every four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.46,0:27:32.88,Main,,0,0,0,,W-Where's my seat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.43,0:27:43.09,Main,,0,0,0,,– Finally.\N– Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.09,0:27:48.52,Main,,0,0,0,,How's your country been?\NYou said it was ravaged by pirates four years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.52,0:27:52.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Fleet Admiral Sakazuki,\Nthey were sent to Impel Down.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.98,0:27:58.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Speaking of pirates, there is one name I'm hearing often lately. I think it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.28,0:28:00.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Straw Hat Luffy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.57,0:28:08.20,Main,,0,0,0,,He attempted to assassinate Big Mom,\Nand rumor has it that he's going after Kaido next.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.20,0:28:13.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Kaido?! {Does that mean Wano\Nwill be in turmoil next?}Does that mean \NWano is next in line for disaster?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.00,0:28:18.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Wano is not affiliated with the World Government,\N{so it's already practically lawless.}which effectively makes it a lawless land.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.59,0:28:23.59,Main,,0,0,0,,{We don't know if it even operates as a country.}We don't even know if it operates as a country.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.59,0:28:27.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Is there nothing we can do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.01,0:28:30.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Sending the Navy would cost money.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.98,0:28:41.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Trouble seems to follow this \NStraw Hat Luffy, wherever he goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.44,0:28:43.07,Main,,0,0,0,,You got that right!{!}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.36,0:28:46.32,Main,,0,0,0,,What's so funny, Prodence?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.16,0:28:49.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,Luffy-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.87,0:28:52.25,Main,,0,0,0,,The position of chairman always rotates.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.25,0:28:53.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Who is it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.87,0:28:56.38,Main,,0,0,0,,{It's me!}I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.38,0:28:58.63,Main,,0,0,0,,{It's a pleasure, everyone.}Everyone, it will be my honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.63,0:29:00.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Ballywood, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.34,0:29:02.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.05,0:29:05.43,Main,,0,0,0,,{I think you'll run things efficiently.}This should run smoothly, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.43,0:29:09.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Even if we have a full seven days,\Nwe have so much to address.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.22,0:29:12.77,Main,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}This is the great conference \Nthat determines the order of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.43,0:29:16.85,Main,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}It is known as...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.65,0:29:21.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Well then... my fellow monarchs...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.24,0:29:29.28,Main,,0,0,0,,let us carefully discuss \Nthe future of this beautiful world!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.04,0:29:35.96,Main,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}the Reverie!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.67,0:29:39.84,Main,,0,0,0,,{It seems like the conference has begun...}And so the conference begins.{..}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.84,0:29:46.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Apparently, King Cobra of Arabasta\Nis requesting an audience with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.72,0:29:48.89,Main,,0,0,0,,The Nefertari family...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.89,0:29:55.64,Main,,0,0,0,,was the only family of the First Twenty,\Nwho stayed in the lower realm 800 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.64,0:30:00.48,Main,,0,0,0,,In a sense, they're traitors.\NHas he noticed something?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.48,0:30:03.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's hope he doesn't make things complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.53,0:30:07.66,Main,,0,0,0,,You {can}could say the same\Nabout the {Big Mom and Kaido situation}situation with Big Mom and Kaido.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.66,0:30:13.54,Main,,0,0,0,,It's been two years since the Summit War.\N {Yet}And yet{...}, this maelstrom will not cease.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.54,0:30:18.88,Main,,0,0,0,,{The balance of the world can not be maintained forever.}This world's equilibrium \Ncannot be maintained indefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.88,0:30:24.67,Main,,0,0,0,,{It seems like a great cleansing is in order.}The time has come for a great cleansing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.64,0:30:37.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Imu-{\i1}sama{\i}.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.14,0:30:40.98,Main,,0,0,0,,{They have arrived.}The {Elder Stars}Five Elders have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.95,0:31:42.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Have you discovered another light \Nto be erased from history?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.58,0:31:45.25,Main,,0,0,0,,{Has the decision been made?}Is it decided, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.01,0:31:52.18,Main,,0,0,0,,If so, you need only give us the name!
